{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":388718,"duration_api_ms":429053,"num_turns":23,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"824981ed-792a-4d43-887a-da09d5bbb4de","total_cost_usd":1.22368525,"usage":{"input_tokens":3230,"cache_creation_input_tokens":60315,"cache_read_input_tokens":566898,"output_tokens":13753,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":60315,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":3230,"outputTokens":13753,"cacheReadInputTokens":566898,"cacheCreationInputTokens":60315,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.0203927499999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":94,"outputTokens":14027,"cacheReadInputTokens":390935,"cacheCreationInputTokens":75176,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2032925,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All three issues are correctly addressed with sound design decisions and thorough test coverage (351 tests pass).\n\n**Issue 1 (Struct drift):** `#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]` on both `StartJournalDetails` and `CompletionJournalDetails` plus dedicated roundtrip tests (`start_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render`, `completion_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render`) provide test-time detection of field additions, removals, and renames between the model payload structs and the fs parsing structs. Acceptance criterion met.\n\n**Issue 2 (Runless-to-named completion):** The `update_task_run` FS method now accepts a runless open match when the caller supplies a `run_id` AND `started_at` matches, correctly backfilling `run_id` and `plan_hash` before finalization. The `started_at` guard prevents wrong-attempt backfilling. Two tests cover the happy path (`runless_start_completed_with_named_run_id`) and the rejection case (`runless_match_rejected_when_started_at_mismatches`). Acceptance criterion met.\n\n**Issue 3 (plan_hash auto-population):** New entries auto-populate `plan_hash` from the milestone snapshot via `snapshot_plan_hash()`. The implementation deliberately does NOT backfill existing rows (running replays or finalization), with well-reasoned comments explaining that `persist_plan()` can advance `snapshot.plan_hash` after the original attempt started, so stamping the current snapshot hash would mislabel a v1 attempt as v2. This is the correct behavior. Five tests cover: auto-population on new entries, explicit caller precedence, terminal replay after plan evolution, legacy open row protection, and legacy terminal replay protection. The `snapshot_plan_hash` function now distinguishes NotFound (returns None silently) from unexpected errors (logs warning), which is a good improvement over the previous `.ok()` blanket suppression. Acceptance criterion met.\n\nNo critical bugs, safety problems, or correctness gaps found.","amendments":[]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"aada6c51-db53-462a-88a4-c2d2ac1f0f7e"}
